# ZZT corpus content policy

Museum ZZT `.zss` scripts under `ops/fixtures/zzt/corpus/zss/` must not contain profanity or slurs in player-facing text.

## Tooling

| Task | Purpose |
|------|---------|
| `yarn task run content:zzt:corpus:profanity:scan` | Report hits → `ops/fixtures/zzt/corpus/profanity-report.json` |
| `yarn task run content:zzt:corpus:sanitize` | Redact hits in place → `sanitize-report.json` |
| `yarn task run content:zzt:corpus:profanity:verify` | Exit 1 if any hits remain (CI) |

Word lists and redaction logic: `zss/feature/content/zztcorpussanitize.ts`.

## Pipeline

`content:zzt:corpus:zss` and `content:zzt:corpus:build` run **sanitize automatically** after `.zss` generation.

Rebuilding zss **without** sanitize wipes manual redaction — always run sanitize after `corpus:zss` if skipping the combined build.

## Redaction rules

- Matched words → `[removed]` (word boundaries only).
- Slur `@stat` / `:label` / `#bind` names → `redacted`.
- Allowlisted false positives: ZZT toolkit *“Colored empty”*, `:wop` labels, *Moby Dick*, color-adjective *“multi-colored”*, etc.

## When editing corpus scripts

1. Do not introduce new profanity or slurs.
2. After bulk zss regen, run `content:zzt:corpus:sanitize` then `content:zzt:corpus:profanity:verify`.
3. Extend `zztcorpussanitize.ts` (terms or allowlist) — not ad-hoc one-off sed.
